    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="123" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rio de
                                    Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22,
                            1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Thompson officially confirms the successes of the Government at Bage and
                        reports the continuance of the fighting at Nictheroy. He transmits the
                        information received by him that the <hi rend="italic">Nictheroy</hi> and
                        two other war vessels of the Government sailed from Pernambuco for the south
                        on the 20th, and says that the situation remains unchanged.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
